attributes.description: Beginning in December 2023, Mandiant identified UNC4531 activity targeting South Korean entities via CABBEACON, which collects victims' system information, lists several directories including desktop, downloads, and documents, and transfers the collected data to a specified remote server. UNC4531 sent phishing emails impersonating the South Korean National Tax Service and containing an archive attachment including malicious shortcut link files that ultimately led to the deployment of CABBEACON. While open-source reporting has attributed UNC4531 activity to North Korean activity clusters APT43 and UNC776 (aligning with what is publicly referred to as "Konni"), Mandiant does not have evidence to corroborate these assessments and currently tracks UNC4531 as an independent cluster.

value.title: HackTool - Powerup Write Hijack DLL
value.author: Subhash Popuri (@pbssubhash)
value.description:
Powerup tool's Write Hijack DLL exploits DLL hijacking for privilege escalation.
In it's default mode, it builds a self deleting .bat file which executes malicious command.
The detection rule relies on creation of the malicious bat file (debug.bat by default).

value.title: Suspicious LNK Command-Line Padding with Whitespace Characters
value.author: Swachchhanda Shrawan Poudel (Nextron Systems)
value.description:
Detects exploitation of LNK file command-line length discrepancy, where attackers hide malicious commands beyond the 260-character UI limit while the actual command-line argument field supports 4096 characters using whitespace padding (e.g., 0x20, 0x09-0x0D).
Adversaries insert non-printable whitespace characters (e.g., Line Feed \x0A, Carriage Return \x0D) to pad the visible section of the LNK file, pushing malicious commands past the UI-visible boundary.
The hidden payload, executed at runtime but invisible in Windows Explorer properties, enables stealthy execution and evasioncommonly used for social engineering attacks.
This rule flags suspicious use of such padding observed in real-world attacks.

value.title: File And SubFolder Enumeration Via Dir Command
value.author: frack113
value.description: Detects usage of the "dir" command part of Windows CMD with the "/S" command line flag in order to enumerate files in a specified directory and all subdirectories.

value.title: File Deletion Via Del
value.author: frack113
value.description:
Detects execution of the builtin "del"/"erase" commands in order to delete files.
Adversaries may delete files left behind by the actions of their intrusion activity.
Malware, tools, or other non-native files dropped or created on a system by an adversary may leave traces to indicate to what was done within a network and how.
Removal of these files can occur during an intrusion, or as part of a post-intrusion process to minimize the adversary's footprint.

value.title: Office Application Initiated Network Connection To Non-Local IP
value.author: Christopher Peacock '@securepeacock', SCYTHE '@scythe_io', Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Tim Shelton, Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description:
Detects an office application (Word, Excel, PowerPoint)  that initiate a network connection to a non-private IP addresses.
This rule aims to detect traffic similar to one seen exploited in CVE-2021-42292.
This rule will require an initial baseline and tuning that is specific to your organization.

value.title: CMD Shell Output Redirect
value.author: frack113
value.description: Detects the use of the redirection character ">" to redicrect information in commandline

value.title: Suspicious New Instance Of An Office COM Object
value.author: Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description:
Detects an svchost process spawning an instance of an office application. This happens when the initial word application creates an instance of one of the Office COM objects such as 'Word.Application', 'Excel.Application', etc.
This can be used by malicious actors to create malicious Office documents with macros on the fly. (See vba2clr project in the references)

value.title: HackTool - Powerup Write Hijack DLL
value.author: Subhash Popuri (@pbssubhash)
value.description:
Powerup tool's Write Hijack DLL exploits DLL hijacking for privilege escalation.
In it's default mode, it builds a self deleting .bat file which executes malicious command.
The detection rule relies on creation of the malicious bat file (debug.bat by default).

value.title: Suspicious Copy From or To System Directory
value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Markus Neis, Tim Shelton (HAWK.IO), Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description:
Detects a suspicious copy operation that tries to copy a program from system (System32, SysWOW64, WinSxS) directories to another on disk.
Often used to move LOLBINs such as 'certutil' or 'desktopimgdownldr' to a different location with a different name in order to bypass detections based on locations.

value.title: Hidden Powershell in Link File Pattern
value.author: frack113
value.description: Detects events that appear when a user click on a link file with a powershell command in it

value.title: Suspicious LNK Command-Line Padding with Whitespace Characters
value.author: Swachchhanda Shrawan Poudel (Nextron Systems)
value.description:
Detects exploitation of LNK file command-line length discrepancy, where attackers hide malicious commands beyond the 260-character UI limit while the actual command-line argument field supports 4096 characters using whitespace padding (e.g., 0x20, 0x09-0x0D).
Adversaries insert non-printable whitespace characters (e.g., Line Feed \x0A, Carriage Return \x0D) to pad the visible section of the LNK file, pushing malicious commands past the UI-visible boundary.
The hidden payload, executed at runtime but invisible in Windows Explorer properties, enables stealthy execution and evasioncommonly used for social engineering attacks.
This rule flags suspicious use of such padding observed in real-world attacks.

value.title: Powershell download payload from hardcoded c2 list
value.author: Joe Security
value.description: Powershell download payload from hardcoded c2 list

value.title: Cscript/Wscript Uncommon Script Extension Execution
value.author: Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects Wscript/Cscript executing a file with an uncommon (i.e. non-script) extension

value.title: Potentially Suspicious WDAC Policy File Creation
value.author: X__Junior
value.description: Detects suspicious Windows Defender Application Control (WDAC) policy file creation from abnormal processes that could be abused by attacker to block EDR/AV components while allowing their own malicious code to run on the system.

value.title: Local Network Connection Initiated By Script Interpreter
value.author: frack113
value.description: Detects a script interpreter (Wscript/Cscript) initiating a local network connection to download or execute a script hosted on a shared folder.

value.title: Outbound Network Connection Initiated By Script Interpreter
value.author: frack113, Florian Roth (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects a script interpreter wscript/cscript opening a network connection to a non-local network. Adversaries may use script to download malicious payloads.

value.title: HackTool - CrackMapExec PowerShell Obfuscation
value.author: Thomas Patzke
value.description: The CrachMapExec pentesting framework implements a PowerShell obfuscation with some static strings detected by this rule.

value.title: Greedy File Deletion Using Del
value.author: frack113 , X__Junior (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects execution of the "del" builtin command to remove files using greedy/wildcard expression. This is often used by malware to delete content of folders that perhaps contains the initial malware infection or to delete evidence.

value.title: Base64 Encoded PowerShell Command Detected
value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects usage of the "FromBase64String" function in the commandline which is used to decode a base64 encoded string

value.title: Potentially Suspicious DMP/HDMP File Creation
value.author: Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects the creation of a file with the ".dmp"/".hdmp" extension by a shell or scripting application such as "cmd", "powershell", etc. Often created by software during a crash. Memory dumps can sometimes contain sensitive information such as credentials. It's best to determine the source of the crash.

value.title: Suspicious Curl.EXE Download
value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects a suspicious curl process start on Windows and outputs the requested document to a local file

value.title: HackTool - LaZagne Execution
value.author: Nasreddine Bencherchali, Swachchhanda Shrawan Poudel (Nextron Systems)
value.description:
Detects the execution of the LaZagne. A utility used to retrieve multiple types of passwords stored on a local computer.
LaZagne has been leveraged multiple times by threat actors in order to dump credentials.

value.title: Suspicious XOR Encoded PowerShell Command Line - PowerShell
value.author: Teymur Kheirkhabarov, Harish Segar (rule)
value.description: Detects suspicious powershell process which includes bxor command, alternative obfuscation method to b64 encoded commands.

value.title: Legitimate Application Dropped Script
value.author: frack113, Florian Roth (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects programs on a Windows system that should not write scripts to disk

value.title: Change Default File Association Via Assoc
value.author: Timur Zinniatullin, oscd.community
value.description:
Detects file association changes using the builtin "assoc" command.
When a file is opened, the default program used to open the file (also called the file association or handler) is checked. File association selections are stored in the Windows Registry and can be edited by users, administrators, or programs that have Registry access or by administrators using the built-in assoc utility. Applications can modify the file association for a given file extension to call an arbitrary program when a file with the given extension is opened.

value.title: Suspicious Scan Loop Network
value.author: frack113
value.description: Adversaries may attempt to get a listing of other systems by IP address, hostname, or other logical identifier on a network that may be used for Lateral Movement from the current system

value.title: Emotet Loader Execution Via .LNK File
value.author: @kostastsale
value.description:
Detects the Emotet Epoch4 loader as reported by @malware_traffic back in 2022.
The ".lnk" file was delivered via phishing campaign.

value.title: DNS Query To Devtunnels Domain
value.author: citron_ninja
value.description: Detects DNS query requests to Devtunnels domains. Attackers can abuse that feature to establish a reverse shell or persistence on a machine.

value.title: Forest Blizzard APT - Process Creation Activity
value.author: Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description:
Detects the execution of specific processes and command line combination.
These were seen being created by Forest Blizzard as described by MSFT.

value.title: HTML Help HH.EXE Suspicious Child Process
value.author: Maxim Pavlunin, Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects a suspicious child process of a Microsoft HTML Help (HH.exe)

value.title: Suspicious Certutil Command Usage
value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), juju4, keepwatch
value.description: Detects a suspicious Microsoft certutil execution with sub commands like 'decode' sub command, which is sometimes used to decode malicious code

value.title: Suspicious HH.EXE Execution
value.author: Maxim Pavlunin
value.description: Detects a suspicious execution of a Microsoft HTML Help (HH.exe)

value.title: Obfuscated IP Download Activity
value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), X__Junior (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects use of an encoded/obfuscated version of an IP address (hex, octal...) in an URL combined with a download command

value.title: Suspicious PowerShell Download
value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects suspicious PowerShell download command

value.title: Suspicious Parent Double Extension File Execution
value.author: frack113, Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detect execution of suspicious double extension files in ParentCommandLine

value.title: File Decoded From Base64/Hex Via Certutil.EXE
value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Jonhnathan Ribeiro, oscd.community
value.description: Detects the execution of certutil with either the "decode" or "decodehex" flags to decode base64 or hex encoded files. This can be abused by attackers to decode an encoded payload before execution

value.title: Suspicious Execution of Hostname
value.author: frack113
value.description: Use of hostname to get information

value.title: HH.EXE Execution
value.author: E.M. Anhaus (originally from Atomic Blue Detections, Dan Beavin), oscd.community
value.description: Detects the execution of "hh.exe" to open ".chm" files.

value.title: Whoami Utility Execution
value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects the execution of whoami, which is often used by attackers after exploitation / privilege escalation

value.title: Suspicious Eventlog Clear
value.author: Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems), Swachchhanda Shrawan Poudel (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects usage of known powershell cmdlets such as "Clear-EventLog" to clear the Windows event logs

value.title: Dllhost.EXE Initiated Network Connection To Non-Local IP Address
value.author: bartblaze
value.description:
Detects dllhost initiating a network connection to a non-local IP address.
Aside from Microsoft own IP range that needs to be excluded. Network communication from Dllhost will depend entirely on the hosted DLL.
An initial baseline is recommended before deployment.

value.title: Remote Thread Created In Shell Application
value.author: Splunk Research Team
value.description:
Detects remote thread creation in command shell applications, such as "Cmd.EXE" and "PowerShell.EXE".
It is a common technique used by malware, such as IcedID, to inject malicious code and execute it within legitimate processes.

value.title: PowerShell Download and Execution Cradles
value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects PowerShell download and execution cradles.

value.title: Suspicious PowerShell Parameter Substring
value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Daniel Bohannon (idea), Roberto Rodriguez (Fix)
value.description: Detects suspicious PowerShell invocation with a parameter substring

value.title: WSF/JSE/JS/VBA/VBE File Execution Via Cscript/Wscript
value.author: Michael Haag
value.description: Detects script file execution (.js, .jse, .vba, .vbe, .vbs, .wsf) by Wscript/Cscript

value.title: Non Interactive PowerShell Process Spawned
value.author: Roberto Rodriguez @Cyb3rWard0g (rule), oscd.community (improvements)
value.description: Detects non-interactive PowerShell activity by looking at the "powershell" process with a non-user GUI process such as "explorer.exe" as a parent.

value.title: Usage Of Web Request Commands And Cmdlets
value.author: James Pemberton / @4A616D6573, Endgame, JHasenbusch, oscd.community, Austin Songer @austinsonger
value.description: Detects the use of various web request commands with commandline tools and Windows PowerShell cmdlets (including aliases) via CommandLine

value.title: Script Interpreter Execution From Suspicious Folder
value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects a suspicious script execution in temporary folders or folders accessible by environment variables

value.title: Usage Of Web Request Commands And Cmdlets - ScriptBlock
value.author: James Pemberton / @4A616D6573
value.description: Detects the use of various web request commands with commandline tools and Windows PowerShell cmdlets (including aliases) via PowerShell scriptblock logs

value.title: CurrentVersion Autorun Keys Modification
value.author: Victor Sergeev, Daniil Yugoslavskiy, Gleb Sukhodolskiy, Timur Zinniatullin, oscd.community, Tim Shelton, frack113 (split)
value.description: Detects modification of autostart extensibility point (ASEP) in registry.

value.title: PowerShell Web Download
value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects suspicious ways to download files or content using PowerShell

value.title: New RUN Key Pointing to Suspicious Folder
value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Markus Neis, Sander Wiebing, Swachchhanda Shrawan Poudel (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects suspicious new RUN key element pointing to an executable in a suspicious folder

value.title: Potential Persistence Attempt Via Run Keys Using Reg.EXE
value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Swachchhanda Shrawan Poudel (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects suspicious command line reg.exe tool adding key to RUN key in Registry

value.title: Direct Autorun Keys Modification
value.author: Victor Sergeev, Daniil Yugoslavskiy, oscd.community, Swachchhanda Shrawan Poudel (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects direct modification of autostart extensibility point (ASEP) in registry using reg.exe.

value.title: Read Contents From Stdin Via Cmd.EXE
value.author: frack113, Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detect the use of "<" to read and potentially execute a file via cmd.exe

value.title: File And SubFolder Enumeration Via Dir Command
value.author: frack113
value.description: Detects usage of the "dir" command part of Windows CMD with the "/S" command line flag in order to enumerate files in a specified directory and all subdirectories.

value.title: Potential Dropper Script Execution Via WScript/CScript
value.author: Margaritis Dimitrios (idea), Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), oscd.community, Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects wscript/cscript executions of scripts located in user directories

value.title: Suspicious Script Execution From Temp Folder
value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Max Altgelt (Nextron Systems), Tim Shelton
value.description: Detects a suspicious script executions from temporary folder

value.title: Scheduled Task Creation Via Schtasks.EXE
value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects the creation of scheduled tasks by user accounts via the "schtasks" utility.

value.title: Potential Binary Or Script Dropper Via PowerShell
value.author: frack113, Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects PowerShell creating a binary executable or a script file.

value.title: Creation of an Executable by an Executable
value.author: frack113
value.description: Detects the creation of an executable by another executable

value.title: Suspicious Binaries and Scripts in Public Folder
value.author: The DFIR Report
value.description: Detects the creation of a file with a suspicious extension in the public folder, which could indicate potential malicious activity.

value.title: PowerShell Initiated Network Connection
value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects a PowerShell process that initiates network connections. Check for suspicious target ports and target systems.

value.title: Schedule Task Creation From Env Variable Or Potentially Suspicious Path Via Schtasks.EXE
value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects Schtask creations that point to a suspicious folder or an environment variable often used by malware

value.title: Hiding Files with Attrib.exe
value.author: Sami Ruohonen
value.description: Detects usage of attrib.exe to hide files from users.

value.title: WmiPrvSE Spawned A Process
value.author: Roberto Rodriguez @Cyb3rWard0g
value.description: Detects WmiPrvSE spawning a process

value.title: File Deletion Via Del
value.author: frack113
value.description:
Detects execution of the builtin "del"/"erase" commands in order to delete files.
Adversaries may delete files left behind by the actions of their intrusion activity.
Malware, tools, or other non-native files dropped or created on a system by an adversary may leave traces to indicate to what was done within a network and how.
Removal of these files can occur during an intrusion, or as part of a post-intrusion process to minimize the adversary's footprint.

value.title: Local Accounts Discovery
value.author: Timur Zinniatullin, Daniil Yugoslavskiy, oscd.community
value.description: Local accounts, System Owner/User discovery using operating systems utilities

value.title: Process Execution From A Potentially Suspicious Folder
value.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Tim Shelton
value.description: Detects a potentially suspicious execution from an uncommon folder.

value.title: Change PowerShell Policies to an Insecure Level
value.author: frack113
value.description: Detects changing the PowerShell script execution policy to a potentially insecure level using the "-ExecutionPolicy" flag.

value.title: Password Protected Compressed File Extraction Via 7Zip
value.author: Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description: Detects usage of 7zip utilities (7z.exe, 7za.exe and 7zr.exe) to extract password protected zip files.

value.title: Suspicious Get-WmiObject
value.author: frack113
value.description: The infrastructure for management data and operations that enables local and remote management of Windows personal computers and servers

value.title: Use Short Name Path in Command Line
value.author: frack113, Nasreddine Bencherchali
value.description: Detect use of the Windows 8.3 short name. Which could be used as a method to avoid command-line detection

value.title: Change PowerShell Policies to an Insecure Level - PowerShell
value.author: frack113
value.description: Detects changing the PowerShell script execution policy to a potentially insecure level using the "Set-ExecutionPolicy" cmdlet.

value.title: Potential Defense Evasion Via Binary Rename
value.author: Matthew Green @mgreen27, Ecco, James Pemberton @4A616D6573, oscd.community, Andreas Hunkeler (@Karneades)
value.description: Detects the execution of a renamed binary often used by attackers or malware leveraging new Sysmon OriginalFileName datapoint.

value.title: CMD Shell Output Redirect
value.author: frack113
value.description: Detects the use of the redirection character ">" to redicrect information in commandline

value.title: Cscript Visual Basic Script Execution
value.author: frack113
value.description: Adversaries may abuse Visual Basic (VB) for execution

value.title: Automated Collection Command Prompt
value.author: frack113
value.description: Once established within a system or network, an adversary may use automated techniques for collecting internal data.

value.title: Office Application Initiated Network Connection To Non-Local IP
value.author: Christopher Peacock '@securepeacock', SCYTHE '@scythe_io', Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Tim Shelton, Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description:
Detects an office application (Word, Excel, PowerPoint)  that initiate a network connection to a non-private IP addresses.
This rule aims to detect traffic similar to one seen exploited in CVE-2021-42292.
This rule will require an initial baseline and tuning that is specific to your organization.

value.title: Suspicious Process Creation
value.author: Florian Roth
value.description: Detects suspicious process starts on Windows systems based on keywords

value.title: Suspicious New Instance Of An Office COM Object
value.author: Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
value.description:
Detects an svchost process spawning an instance of an office application. This happens when the initial word application creates an instance of one of the Office COM objects such as 'Word.Application', 'Excel.Application', etc.
This can be used by malicious actors to create malicious Office documents with macros on the fly. (See vba2clr project in the references)
